    <x-sections.card-detailed-info
        heading="5 Ways Floor Graphics Work Harder for Your Business Than You Realize"
        image1="/images/window-wall-floor-decals/top5pct-banner-wall-decal-door-signs-joliet.jpg"
        alt1="Custom floor graphics and floor decals for businesses in Joliet, Will and DuPage County Illinois"
    >
        <x-slot name="intro">
            <p class="mb-4">Most businesses think about wall signs, window graphics, and exterior signage when planning their visual environment, but floor graphics are one of the most overlooked and high-impact signage investments available. Every square foot of your floor is potential advertising space, and customers instinctively look down as they walk, which means a well-placed floor graphic gets seen constantly, especially when paired with coordinating <a href="/signs/business-signs/wall-signs" class="link-notification">wall signs</a> that guide the eye from floor to wall. Here are five ways floor graphics create real value for businesses in Joliet and throughout Will and DuPage County.</p>
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">1. They Guide Customers Without Staff Effort</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">One of the most practical applications for floor graphics is wayfinding, directing customers to specific areas, checkouts, entrances, exits, waiting areas, or product displays without requiring staff to provide directions. A well-placed arrow or zone marker on the floor reduces customer confusion, speeds up their navigation through your space, and improves their overall experience. This is especially valuable in larger retail environments, medical offices, schools, and any space where multiple pathways exist.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="mid">
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">2. They Create Powerful Point-of-Purchase Impact</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">A floor graphic placed directly in front of a product display draws the customer's eye to that specific product and reinforces the promotional message from a different angle than surrounding shelf and wall signage, and it works even more powerfully when it coordinates with matching <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> and exterior banners running the same campaign. Studies on retail environments consistently show that point-of-purchase displays that use multiple sign surfaces generate significantly higher product engagement and conversion, and adding a floor graphic to your existing promotional mix is an inexpensive way to amplify your current campaigns using our <a href="/signs/business-signs/banners" class="link-notification">banners</a> and floor graphics together.</p>
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">3. They Reinforce Brand Identity Throughout Your Space</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Branded floor graphics, those featuring your logo, brand colors, tagline, or brand pattern, extend your visual brand identity into a dimension of your space that most businesses leave completely unbranded. A logo on your floor at the entrance, brand colors incorporated into a floor runner graphic, or your company tagline printed large on a waiting area floor all communicate professionalism and intentionality that customers notice and remember, and they coordinate naturally with our <a href="/signs/business-signs/door-signs" class="link-notification">frosted door signs</a> for a complete privacy and branding environment. Brand-consistent environments build trust and perceived value.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="lower">
            <h3 class="text-h3 font-bold text-charcoal mb-2">4. They Are Safe and Code-Compliant</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Our floor graphics are printed on laminated non-slip vinyl that meets commercial safety standards for floor surfaces. The slip-resistant laminate makes your floor graphic safe in both dry and light-moisture conditions, and we use the same professional installation standards we apply to all our <a href="/signs/business-signs/window-signs" class="link-notification">window signs</a> and interior graphics projects throughout Will and DuPage County. We do not produce floor graphics that create slip hazards, and every product we install is inspected before we leave your space, with the same care we bring to our <a href="/signs/business-signs/wall-signs" class="link-notification">wall sign</a> installations and exterior signage projects.</p>
        </x-slot>
        <x-slot name="footer">
            <p class="mb-4">We are a veteran owned print shop at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet, Illinois. We design, print, and install floor graphics for businesses throughout Will and DuPage County and the greater Chicagoland area, and our full <a href="/signs" class="link-notification">signs shop</a> means floor decals, window signs, banners, and yard signs can all be ordered together. We focus on quality, accuracy, and long-term durability in every project, and many of our clients complete their branded space by adding coordinating <a href="/custom-apparel" class="link-notification">custom apparel</a> for staff so the brand environment is consistent from the floor to the team uniforms.</p>
            <p>Call us at (815) 349 8600 to discuss your floor graphic project today, from a single floor decal to a complete floor signage program for your facility, and ask about pairing with our <a href="/signs/business-signs/wall-signs" class="link-notification">wall signs</a> for a complete interior brand installation.</p>
        </x-slot>
    </x-sections.card-detailed-info>

